swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.name: swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus
swDevInfoFrontPanelLedStatus.description: This object is a set of system LED indications. The first two octets indicate the LED PoE mode. 01 02 = PoE Mode 02 01 = Normal Mode 00 00 = Non-PoE Device The next two are defined as system LED. The third octet is power LED. 0x01 : Power Off 0x02 : Power On the forth octet is console led: 0x01 = system start up 0x02 = a user is login through console 0x03 = no user is login through console The fifth octect is RPS (Redundancy Power Supply) LED. 0x01 = Ineternal Power working 0x02 = External Power working The sixth octect is FAN LED 0x01 = Fan LED Off 0x02 = Fan LED blinking The other octets following are the logical port LED (following dot1dBasePort ordering). Every two bytes are presented to a port. The first byte is presentd to the Link/Activity LED. The second byte is presented to the Speed LED. Link/Activity LED: The most significant bit is used for blink/solid: 8 = The LED blinks. The second significant bit is used for link status: 1 = link fail. 2 = link pass. Speed LED: Normal Mode bit 4 : 0 = copper link up (if link fail will show 0) 1 = fibber link up bit 2-0 : 01 = 10Mbps. 02 = 100Mbps. 03 = 1000Mbps. 04 = 10000Mbps POE mode: 01 = no PD connected. 02 = no deliver power to PD. 03 = deliver power to PD.

The specific function of each port will depend on the per port LLDP setting. For the advertisement of LLDP packets, the switch announces the information to its neighbor through ports. For receiving LLDP packets, the switch will learn the information from the LLDP packets advertised from the neighbor in the neighbor table.

swL2DevCtrlLLDPForwardMessageState.description: When lldp is disabled and lldp forward_message's are enabled, the LLDP Data Unit packets received by the switch will be forwarded.

swL2DevCtrlVLANTrunkState.description: This indicates the global state of the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2DevAlarmNewRoot.description: When the device has become the new root of the Spanning Tree, this object decides whether to send a new root trap.

swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.name: swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange
swL2DevAlarmTopologyChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the switch topology changes. If the object is enabled (3), the Topology Change trap is sent by the device when any of its configured ports transition from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. For the same port transition, the device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or in another state.

swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.name: swL2DevAlarmLinkChange
swL2DevAlarmLinkChange.description: This object determines whether or not to send a trap message when the link changes. If the object is enabled (3), the Link Change trap is sent by the device when any of its port links change. The device does not send the trap if this object value is disabled or in another state.

swL2VlanStaticTable.description: A table containing static configuration information for each VLAN configured into the device by (local or network) management. All entries are permanent and will be restored after the device is reset.

swL2VlanIndex.name: swL2VlanIndex

swL2VLANAdvertisement.name: swL2VLANAdvertisement

swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.name: swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState
swL2PVIDAutoAssignmentState.description: This object controls the PVID auto assignment state. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is disabled, the PVID can only be changed by PVID configuration (user changes explicitly). The VLAN configuration will not automatically change the PVID. If 'Auto-assign PVID' is enabled, the PVID will be changed by PVID or VLAN configuration. When a user configures a port to VLAN X's untagged membership, this port's PVID will be updated with VLAN X. Using the VLAN list command, PVID is updated as the last item of the VLAN list. When a user removes a port from the untagged membership of the PVID's VLAN, the port's PVID will be assigned 'default VLAN'.

If auto-negotiation signaling is disabled, a write to this object has no effect. Setting the value of this object to norestart(2) has no effect.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisCableStatus.description: This object indicates the cable status.

swL2PortCableDiagnosisPairLength.description: This object indicates the approx. length or length to failure of the pair. The unit value is in meters.

swL2PortErrPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module).

swL2PortErrPortState.name: swL2PortErrPortState
swL2PortErrPortState.description: This object indicates if the port state is enabled or disabled.

swL2PortErrPortConnStatus.name: swL2PortErrPortConnStatus
swL2PortErrPortConnStatus.description: This object indicates whether the Port Status is err-disabled or not.

swL2PortErrPortReason.name: swL2PortErrPortReason
swL2PortErrPortReason.description: This object describes the reason for the port error disabled type.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable
swL2PortAutoNegInfoTable.description: A table that contains information about every port's auto negotiation status.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus
swL2PortAutoNegInfoAdminStatus.description: If the value of this object is disabled(2) then the interface will act as it would if it had no auto-negotiation signaling. The status is affect by setting swL2PortCtrlNwayState.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits
swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapabilityBits.description: A value that uniquely identifies the set of capabilities of the local auto-negotiation entity. Note that interfaces that support this MIB may have capabilities that extend beyond the scope of this MIB. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may support some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapAdvertisedBits

Capabilities in this object that are not available in swL2PortAutoNegCapabilityBits cannot be enabled. Note that the local auto-negotiation entity may advertise some capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits.name: swL2PortAutoNegInfoCapReceivedBits

Note that interfaces that support this MIB may be attached to remote auto-negotiation entities that have capabilities beyond the scope of this MIB. This is indicated by returning the bit value bOther in addition to any bit values for standard capabilities that are listed in the IANAifMauAutoNegCapBits TC.

swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex.name: swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex
swL2PortDropCounterPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2PortBufferFullDrops.name: swL2PortBufferFullDrops
swL2PortBufferFullDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded while buffer full.

swL2PortACLDrops.name: swL2PortACLDrops
swL2PortACLDrops.description: The total number of packets denied by ACLs.

swL2PortMulticastDrops.name: swL2PortMulticastDrops
swL2PortMulticastDrops.description: The total number of multicast packet that is discarded.

swL2PortVLANIngressDrops.name: swL2PortVLANIngressDrops
swL2PortVLANIngressDrops.description: The total number of packets discarded by VLAN ingress checking.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlTable.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlTable
swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlTable.description: A table that contains information for each port's jumbo frame information.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlEntry.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlEntry
swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlEntry.description: A list of information for each port's jumbo frame of the device.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlPortIndex
swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.

swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlState.name: swL2PortJumboFrameCtrlState

DSCP (2) --- indicates if the associated port's DSCP control information is in the swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlTable will take effect upon replacement of the DSCP(DiffServ codepoint) field. swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlTable.name: swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlTable

swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlPortIndex
swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlMode.name: swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlMode
swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlMode.description: The DSCP mode of this port. dscp-Force-Overwrite(1) --- The DSCP field for the IP packet is replaced by the specific value regardless of the DSCP of the incoming packet. dscp-Change-If-Zero(2) --- The DSCP field for the IP packet is replaced by the specific value if the DSCP of the incoming packet is zero.

swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlValue.name: swL2DiffServDSCPCtrlValue

swL2DiffServTOSCtrlPortIndex.name: swL2DiffServTOSCtrlPortIndex
swL2DiffServTOSCtrlPortIndex.description: This object indicates the module's port number.(1..Max port number in the module)

swL2DiffServTOSCtrlMode.name: swL2DiffServTOSCtrlMode

swL2DiffServTOSCtrlValue.name: swL2DiffServTOSCtrlValue
swL2DiffServTOSCtrlValue.description: This object is used only if swL2DiffServTOSCtrlMode is tos-Force-Overwrite(1)

swL2MulticastFilterProfileTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileTable
swL2MulticastFilterProfileTable.description: A table that contains information about multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileEntry
swL2MulticastFilterProfileEntry.description: A list of information for each multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileName.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileName
swL2MulticastFilterProfileName.description: Specifies a profile name for each multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterStatus.name: swL2MulticastFilterStatus
swL2MulticastFilterStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressTable
swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressTable.description: A table that contains information about multicast filter address.

swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressEntry
swL2MulticastFilterProfileAddressEntry.description: A list of information for each multicast filter address.

swL2MulticastFilterFromIp.name: swL2MulticastFilterFromIp
swL2MulticastFilterFromIp.description: Specifies the head IP address of a multicast address range which will be binded to a multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterToIp.name: swL2MulticastFilterToIp
swL2MulticastFilterToIp.description: Specifies the tail IP address of a multicast address range which will be binded to a multicast filter profile.

swL2MulticastFilterAddressState.name: swL2MulticastFilterAddressState
swL2MulticastFilterAddressState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. Setting value to createAndGo (4) will add the multicast address list specified in swL2MulticastFilterFromIp and swL2MulticastFilterToIp to multicast filter profile. Setting value to destroy (6) will remove the multicast address list specified in swL2MulticastFilterFromIp and swL2MulticastFilterToIp from multicast filter profile.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortTable.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortTable
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortTable.description: A table that is used to bind the port to the profile ID.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortEntry.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortEntry
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortEntry.description: A list of information that is used to bind the port to the profile ID.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortIndex.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortIndex
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortIndex.description: Specifies the port as an index.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortAccess.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortAccess
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortAccess.description: This object indicates the access status for each port.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID.description: This object specifies a profile ID list for each port.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileSta.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileStatus
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileSta.description: Controls the multicast filter profile list which binds to each port. When set to add (2), the multicast filter profile ID list which is specified in swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID will be bound to the port. When set to delete (3), the multicast filter profile ID list that is specified in swL2LimitedMulticastFilterPortProfileID will be unbound from the port. The attribute value reverts to 'other' once the action has been done.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupTable
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupTable.description: A table that contains information about max group numbers based on each port.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupEntry.description: A list of max group number information for each port.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupPortIndex.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupPortIndex
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroupPortIndex.description: Specifies the port number as a table index.

swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroup.name: swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroup
swL2MulticastFilterPortMaxGroup.description: Specifies maximum multicast filter group numbers for each port. The default value is 256.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDTable.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDTable
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDTable.description: A table that is used to bind the VID to the profile ID.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDEntry.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDEntry
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDEntry.description: A list of information that is used to bind the VID to the profile ID.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDIndex.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDIndex
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDIndex.description: Specifies the VID as an index.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDAccess.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDAccess
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDAccess.description: This object indicates the access status for each VID.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileID.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileID
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileID.description: This object specifies a profile ID list for each VID.

swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileStat.name: swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileStatus
swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileStat.description: Controls the multicast filter profile list which binds to each VID. When set to add (2), the multicast filter profile ID list which is specified in swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileID will be bound to the VID. When set to delete (3), the multicast filter profile ID list that is specified in swL2LimitedMulticastFilterVIDProfileID will be unbound from the VID. The attribute value reverts to 'other' once the action has been done.

swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupTable.name: swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupTable
swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupTable.description: A table that contains information about max group numbers based on VID.

swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupEntry.name: swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupEntry
swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupEntry.description: A list of max group number information for each VID.

swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupVIDIndex.name: swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupVIDIndex
swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroupVIDIndex.description: Specifies the VID number as a table index.

swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroup.name: swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroup
swL2MulticastFilterVIDMaxGroup.description: Specifies maximum multicast filter group numbers for each VID. The default value is 256.

swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.name: swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry
swL2QOSBandwidthControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOSBandwidthControlTable.

swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRxRate.description: Indicates RX Rate (Mbit/sec) of the specified port. A value of 10000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthTxRate.description: Indicates TX Rate(Mbit/sec) of the specified port. A value of 10000 means no limit.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusRxRate.description: The Rx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Rx Rate.

swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.name: swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate
swL2QOSBandwidthRadiusTxRate.description: The Tx Rate value comes from the RADIUS server, If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the locally configured Tx Rate.

swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.name: swL2QOSSchedulingEntry
swL2QOSSchedulingEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOSSchedulingTable.

swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts
swL2QOSSchedulingMaxPkts.description: Indicates the maximum number of packets the hardware priority queue will be allowed to transmit before allowing the next lowest priority queue to transmit its packets. a value between 0 and 15 can be specified.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanism.description: Indicates the mechanism of QoS scheduling.

swL2QOSSchedulingMaxLatency.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMaxLatency
swL2QOSSchedulingMaxLatency.description: Indicates the maximum amount of time the hardware priority queue will be allowed to transmit packets before allowing the next lowest priority queue to begin transmitting its packets. A value between 0 and 255 can be specified- with this value multiplied by 16 ms to arrive at the total allowed time for the queue to transmit packets. For example, a value of 3 specifies 3*16=48 ms. The queue will continue transmitting the last packet until it finishes when the max_latency timer expires.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.name: swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass
swL2QOS8021pUserPriorityClass.description: The number of the switch's hardware priority queue. The switch has seven hardware priority queues available. They are numbered between 0 (the lowest priority) and 6 (the highest priority).

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriorityTable.

swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority
swL2QOS8021pDefaultPriority.description: The priority value assigned to untagged packets received by the ports on the switch.

swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.name: swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority
swL2QOS8021pRadiusPriority.description: Indicates the value of 802.1p comes from RADIUS server. If an 802.1X port is authenticated, this value will overwrite the local configured value.

swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.name: swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl
swL2QOSSchedulingMechanismCtrl.description: This object controls the QoS scheduling mechanism.

swL2PortSecurityControlTable.name: swL2PortSecurityControlTable
swL2PortSecurityControlTable.description: A port security feature which controls the address learning capability and traffic forwarding decisions. Each port can be enabled or disabled for this function. When it is enabled and a number is given, e.g N this will allow N addresses to be learned on this port, the first N address learned will be locked at this port as static entries. When the learned addresses number reaches N, any incoming packet without learned source addresses are discarded (e.g. dropped) and no more new addresses can be learned on this port.

swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.name: swL2PortSecurityControlEntry
swL2PortSecurityControlEntry.description: A list of information contained in the swL2PortSecurityControlTable.

swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.name: swL2PortSecurityPortIndex
swL2PortSecurityPortIndex.description: Indicates the secured port to lock address learning.

swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.name: swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr
swL2PortSecurityMaxLernAddr.description: Indicates allowable number of addresses that can be learned on this port.

swL2PortSecurityMode.name: swL2PortSecurityMode
swL2PortSecurityMode.description: Indicates the locking address mode. In deleteOnTimeout (3) mode - the locked addresses can be aged out after the aging timer expires. In this mode, when the locked address has aged out, the number of addresses that can be learned has to be increased by one. In deleteOnReset (4) mode - Locked addresses never age out unless the system restarts which will prevent port movement or intrusion.

swL2PortSecurityAdmState.name: swL2PortSecurityAdmState
swL2PortSecurityAdmState.description: Indicates the administration state of the locking address.

swL2PortSecurityEntryClearCtrl.name: swL2PortSecurityEntryClearCtrl
swL2PortSecurityEntryClearCtrl.description: Used to clear port security entries by port. Setting this value to 'start' will execute the clear action, Once cleared, the value returns to 'other'.

swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.name: swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState
swL2PortSecurityTrapLogState.description: When enabled (2), whenever there's a new MAC address that violates the pre-defined port security configuration, traps will be sent out and the relevant information will be logged into the system.

swL2DhcpRelayState.name: swL2DhcpRelayState
swL2DhcpRelayState.description: This object indicates if the DHCP relay function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.name: swL2DhcpRelayHopCount
swL2DhcpRelayHopCount.description: This object indicates the maximum number of router hops that DHCP packets can cross.

swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.name: swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold
swL2DhcpRelayTimeThreshold.description: This object indicates the minimum time in seconds within which the switch must relay the DHCP request. If this time is exceeded, the switch will drop the DHCP packet.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82State
swL2DhcpRelayOption82State.description: This object indicates if the DHCP relay agent information option 82 function is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Check.description: This object indicates if the checking mechanism of DHCP relay agent information option 82 is enabled or disabled.

swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.name: swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy
swL2DhcpRelayOption82Policy.description: This object indicates the reforwarding policy of the DHCP relay agent information option 82. replace (1) - replace the exiting option 82 field in messages. drop (2) - discard messages with an existing option 82 field. keep (3) - retain the existing option 82 field messages.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlTable.description: This table specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlEntry.description: A list of information that specifies the IP address as a destination to forward (relay) DHCP packets to.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlInterfaceName.description: The name of the IP interface.

swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.name: swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState
swL2DhcpRelayCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other (1) - This entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. invalid (2) - Writing this value to the object will remove the corresponding entry from the table. valid (3) - This entry resides in the table.

swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.name: swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries
swL2TrunkMaxSupportedEntries.description: Maximum number of entries in the trunk configuration table (swL2TrunkCtrlTable).

swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.name: swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries
swL2TrunkCurrentNumEntries.description: Current active number of entries in the trunk configuration table.

swL2TrunkCtrlTable.name: swL2TrunkCtrlTable
swL2TrunkCtrlTable.description: This table specifies information about the logical port trunk groups.

swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.name: swL2TrunkCtrlEntry
swL2TrunkCtrlEntry.description: A list of information about each logical port trunk group.

swL2TrunkIndex.name: swL2TrunkIndex
swL2TrunkIndex.description: The index number of the logical port trunk group. The trunk group number depends on the existence of unit and module.

swL2TrunkName.name: swL2TrunkName
swL2TrunkName.description: The name of the logical port trunk group.

swL2TrunkMasterPort.name: swL2TrunkMasterPort
swL2TrunkMasterPort.description: This object indicates the master port number of the port trunk entry. When using Port Trunking, you cannot configure the other ports of the group except the master port. Their configuration must be the same as the master port (e.g. speed, duplex, enabled/disabled, flow control, and so on).

swL2TrunkMember.name: swL2TrunkMember
swL2TrunkMember.description: Indicates the number of ports included in this Trunk group. The trunk port number depends on the existence of the module. The maximum number of ports is 8 for one trunk group.

swL2TrunkFloodingPort.name: swL2TrunkFloodingPort
swL2TrunkFloodingPort.description: The object indicates the flooding port number of the port trunk entry. The first port of the Trunk group is implicitly configured to be the flooding port.

swL2TrunkType.name: swL2TrunkType
swL2TrunkType.description: This object indicates the type of trunk group. static: is a static trunk group lacp: is a LACP trunk group.

swL2TrunkState.name: swL2TrunkState
swL2TrunkState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2TrunkAlgorithm.name: swL2TrunkAlgorithm
swL2TrunkAlgorithm.description: This object configures part of the packet examined by the switch when selecting the egress port for transmitting load-sharing data.

swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortTable
swL2TrunkLACPPortTable.description: This table specifies which ports are grouped together (this can be up to 8 ports) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry
swL2TrunkLACPPortEntry.description: A list of information specifying which ports are grouped together (this can be up to 8 ports) into a single logical link.

swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex
swL2TrunkLACPPortIndex.description: The index of logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkLACPPortState.name: swL2TrunkLACPPortState
swL2TrunkLACPPortState.description: The state of a logical port LACP.

swL2TrunkVLANTable.name: swL2TrunkVLANTable
swL2TrunkVLANTable.description: This table is used to manage the VLAN trunking feature of the device.

swL2TrunkVLANEntry.name: swL2TrunkVLANEntry
swL2TrunkVLANEntry.description: This object is used to configure the VLAN trunking settings for each port.

swL2TrunkVLANPort.name: swL2TrunkVLANPort
swL2TrunkVLANPort.description: This object indicates the port being configured.

swL2TrunkVLANState.name: swL2TrunkVLANState
swL2TrunkVLANState.description: The state of the logical port LACP.

swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort
swL2MirrorLogicTargetPort.description: This object indicates which switch port will sniff another port. A trunk port member cannot be configured as a target snooping port. The port number is the sequential (logical) number, which is also applied to the bridge MIB, etc.

swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress
swL2MirrorPortSourceIngress.description: This represents the port where ingress packets will be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.name: swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress
swL2MirrorPortSourceEgress.description: This represents the port where egress packets will be sniffed.

swL2MirrorPortState.name: swL2MirrorPortState
swL2MirrorPortState.description: This object indicates the port mirroring state. other (1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disabled (2) - After writing this value to the object, the corresponding entry will be removed from the table. enabled (3) - This entry resides in the table.

swL2MirrorGroupTable.name: swL2MirrorGroupTable
swL2MirrorGroupTable.description: This table specifies information about the mirror group configuration.

swL2MirrorGroupEntry.name: swL2MirrorGroupEntry
swL2MirrorGroupEntry.description: A list of information about each mirror group configuration.

swL2MirrorGroupID.name: swL2MirrorGroupID
swL2MirrorGroupID.description: This object indicates the mirror group. The range of this object is (1..N), the value of N is project dependent.

swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus.name: swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus
swL2MirrorGroupRowStatus.description: This object indicates the status of this entry.

swL2MirrorGroupState.name: swL2MirrorGroupState
swL2MirrorGroupState.description: This object indicates the mirror group state.

swL2MirrorGroupTargetPort.name: swL2MirrorGroupTargetPort
swL2MirrorGroupTargetPort.description: This object indicates the mirror group target port.

swL2MirrorGroupSourceIngress.name: swL2MirrorGroupSourceIngress
swL2MirrorGroupSourceIngress.description: This object indicates the mirror group ingress source ports.

swL2MirrorGroupSourceEngress.name: swL2MirrorGroupSourceEngress
swL2MirrorGroupSourceEngress.description: This object indicates the mirror group engress source ports.

swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.name: swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans
swL2IGMPMaxSupportedVlans.description: Maximum number of VLANs in the layer 2 IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.name: swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan
swL2IGMPMaxIpGroupNumPerVlan.description: Maximum number of multicast IP groups per VLAN in the layer 2 IGMP information table.

swL2IGMPSnoopingMulticastVlanState.name: swL2IGMPSnoopingMulticastVlanState
swL2IGMPSnoopingMulticastVlanState.description: It indicates the global state of igmp_snoop multicast_vlan.

swL2IGMPCtrlTable.name: swL2IGMPCtrlTable
swL2IGMPCtrlTable.description: The table controls the VLAN's IGMP function. Its scale depends on the current VLAN state (swL2VlanInfoStatus). If the VLAN is disabled, there is only one entry in the table, with an index of 1. If the VLAN is in Port-Base or 802.1q mode, the maximum number of entries can be 12, with an index range from 1 to 12.

swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.name: swL2IGMPCtrlEntry
swL2IGMPCtrlEntry.description: The entry in IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable). The entry is effective only when IGMP capture switch (swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping) is enabled.

swL2IGMPCtrlVid.name: swL2IGMPCtrlVid
swL2IGMPCtrlVid.description: This object indicates the IGMP control entry's VLAN ID. If the VLAN is disabled, the VID is always 0 and cannot be changed by management users. If the VLAN is in Port-Based mode, the VID is arranged from 1 to 12, in a fixed form. If the VLAN is in 802.1q mode, the VID setting can be changed to a number from 1 to 4094 by the management user, and the VID in each entry must be unique within the IGMP Control Table.

swL2IGMPQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPQueryInterval
swL2IGMPQueryInterval.description: The frequency at which IGMP Host-Query packets are transmitted on this switch.

swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.name: swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime
swL2IGMPMaxResponseTime.description: The maximum query response time on this switch.

swL2IGMPRobustness.name: swL2IGMPRobustness
swL2IGMPRobustness.description: The Robustness Variable allows tuning for the expected packet loss on a subnet. If a subnet is expected to have a high packet loss, the Robustness Variable may be increased. IGMP is robust to (Robustness Variable-1) packet losses.

swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.name: swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval
swL2IGMPLastMemberQueryInterval.description: The Last Member Query Interval is the Max Response Time inserted into Group-Specific Queries sent in response to Leave Group messages, and is also the amount of time between Group-Specific Query messages.

swL2IGMPHostTimeout.name: swL2IGMPHostTimeout
swL2IGMPHostTimeout.description: The timer value for sending IGMP query packets when none were sent by the host on the LAN. The timer works on a per-VLAN basis. Our device will be activated to send the query messages if the timer expires. Please reference RFC2236-1997.

swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.name: swL2IGMPRouteTimeout
swL2IGMPRouteTimeout.description: The Router Timeout is how long a host must wait after hearing a Query before it may send any IGMPv2 messages.

swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.name: swL2IGMPLeaveTimer
swL2IGMPLeaveTimer.description: When a query receives a Leave Group message for a group that has group members on the reception interface, it sends Group-Specific Queries every swL2IGMPLeaveTimer to the group being left.

swL2IGMPQueryState.name: swL2IGMPQueryState
swL2IGMPQueryState.description: This object decides if the IGMP query is enabled or disabled.

swL2IGMPCurrentState.name: swL2IGMPCurrentState
swL2IGMPCurrentState.description: This object indicates the current IGMP query state.

swL2IGMPCtrlState.name: swL2IGMPCtrlState
swL2IGMPCtrlState.description: This object indicates the status of this entry. other (1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable (2) - IGMP function is disabled for this entry. enable (3) - IGMP function is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.name: swL2IGMPFastLeaveState
swL2IGMPFastLeaveState.description: This object indicates the fast_leave status of this entry. other (1) - this entry is currently in use but the conditions under which it will remain so are different from each of the following values. disable (2) - IGMP fast-leave function is disabled for this entry. enable (3) - IGMP fast-leave function is enabled for this entry.

swL2IGMPQueryVersion.name: swL2IGMPQueryVersion
swL2IGMPQueryVersion.description: Configure the IGMP version of query packet which will be sent by the router.

swL2IGMPRateLimit.name: swL2IGMPRateLimit
swL2IGMPRateLimit.description: Config the rate of IGMP report or leave packet that the switch can process on a specific VLAN. The rate is specified in packet per second. The packet that exceeds the limited rate will be dropped. This setting is also applied to multicast VLAN. The default setting '0' is no_limit.

swL2IGMPReportSuppression.name: swL2IGMPReportSuppression
swL2IGMPReportSuppression.description: When enabled, multiple IGMP reports or leaves for a specific group (S,G) will be integrated into only one report before being sent to the router port.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable
swL2IGMPQueryInfoTable.description: This table contains the current number of IGMP query packets which are captured by this device, as well as the IGMP query packets sent by the device.

swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry
swL2IGMPQueryInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP query information, provided that swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrState of the associated VLAN entries are all enabled.

swL2IGMPInfoVid.name: swL2IGMPInfoVid
swL2IGMPInfoVid.description: This object indicates the VID of the associated IGMP info table entry. It follows swL2IGMPCtrlVid in the associated entry of IGMP control table (swL2IGMPCtrlTable).

swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoQueryCount.description: This object indicates the number of query packets received since the IGMP function was enabled, on a per-VLAN basis.

swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.name: swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount
swL2IGMPInfoTxQueryCount.description: This object indicates the send count of IGMP query messages, on a per-VLAN basis. In the case of an IGMP timer expiration, the switch will send IGMP query packets to all related VLAN member ports and increment this object by 1.

swL2IGMPQueryIPAddress.name: swL2IGMPQueryIPAddress
swL2IGMPQueryIPAddress.description: This object identifies the Query IP addresses.

swL2IGMPQueryExpiryTime.name: swL2IGMPQueryExpiryTime
swL2IGMPQueryExpiryTime.description: This object indicates the Query Expiry Time.

swL2IGMPInfoTable.name: swL2IGMPInfoTable
swL2IGMPInfoTable.description: The table containing current IGMP information which was captured by this device, provided that the swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and swL2IGMPCtrlState of the associated VLAN entries are all enabled. Note that the priority of IGMP table entries is lower than the Filtering Table, i.e. if there is a table hash collision between entries in the IGMP Table and Filtering Table inside the switch's H/W address table, then the Filtering Table entry overwrites the colliding entry of the IGMP Table. Also see the swL2FilterMgmt description.

swL2IGMPInfoEntry.name: swL2IGMPInfoEntry
swL2IGMPInfoEntry.description: Information about current IGMP information which was captured by this device, provided that the swL2DevCtrlIGMPSnooping and the swL2IGMPCtrlState of associated VLAN entries are all enabled.

swL2IGMPVid.name: swL2IGMPVid
swL2IGMPVid.description: This object indicates the VID of individual IGMP table entries. It shows the VID IGMP report information captured on the network.

swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr.name: swL2IGMPGroupIpAddr

swL2IGMPPortMap.name: swL2IGMPPortMap
swL2IGMPPortMap.description: This object indicates which ports belong to the same multicast group, on a per-VLAN basis. Each multicast group has an octet string which is indicated by a port map. The most significant bit represents the lowest numbered port, and the least significant bit represents the highest numbered port. Thus, each port of the switch is represented by a single bit within the value of this object. If that bit has a value of '1' then that port is included in the set of ports; the port is not included if its bit has a value of '0'(Note that the setting of the bits corresponding to the port from which a frame is received is irrelevant). The 4 octets represent one unit port according to its logical port. If the unit is less than 32 ports, other ports are not affected and are replaced with zeroes.
